parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Screws Coming Through Side Rails on Bed
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The screws coming through the side rails on the bed can cause damage to the bed and surrounding areas, and potentially lead to injury or discomfort for occupants.

potential injury or discomfort for occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failed A/C compressor can cause discomfort, inconvenience, and potentially lead to overheating or electrical issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Body and Frame Rubber Strip Misalignment
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The misalignment of the rubber strips between the frame and body can cause water to seep into the vehicle, leading to rust and corrosion, which can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle and potentially affect its safety.
symptoms: Water leaks into the vehicle
rust or corrosion on the frame or body
uneven gaps between the frame and body
loose or detached rubber strips.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A poorly fitting basement door can allow water to enter the vehicle, leading to rust and corrosion, and potentially causing electrical issues or other problems.
symptoms: Water leaks into the vehicle

difficulty opening or closing the door.
